passages.text: Strong growth across segments in 1H25; optimistic on Al momentum and growth outlook, reiterate OW

Key takeaways from Huaqin earnings call include: 1) strong earnings growth of \(46\%\) yoy in 1H25 was driven by accelerating Al server delivery and strong momentum in smartphone/PC/wearable areas; 2) GPM dropped sequentially in 2Q25, due to product mix change, but is expected to recover with a better mix; 3) management expects \(>Rmb40bn\) datacenter revenue in 2025 and further growth ahead, given continuous demand from CSPs and Huaqin's full- stack portfolio with share- gain potential; and 4) an unchanged target of a \(\sim 17\%\) revenue CAGR and stronger earnings growth with margin expansion in 2024- 30. We consider Huaqin's growth outlook to be intact, supported by strong momentum across its diversified layout; reiterate OW with a Jun- 26 PT of Rmb115.

Highlights of the 1H25 results. Huaqin achieved \(116\% /128\%\) yoy revenue growth in its intelligent terminal/high performance computing segments in 1H25, which was driven not only by accelerating Al server delivery, but also helped by growing market share in smartphone, PC and wearables (with portfolio expansion). The GPM dropped sequentially by 1.3ppt to \(7.1\%\) , due to revenue mix change (rising contribution from low- margin Al server), but is expected to recover, backed by an improving mix, especially with an increasing contribution from high- margin wearables and switches.

Optimistic outlook for 2H25; unchanged compound growth target. While GPU supply uncertainty remains, Huaqin expects \(>Rmb40bn\) datacenter revenue and \(>Rmb160bn\) total revenue for 2025, with strong growth in the smartphone, PC, and wearables segments continuing in 2H25. Management addressed its optimistic outlook for robust demand in the Al space, believing its full- stack product portfolio (covering Al server, general server and switch) will support its share gains and persistent revenue growth (with improving margin from a better mix). Huaqin also stated an unchanged target of a \(\sim 17\%\) revenue CAGR and stronger earnings growth for 2024- 30, with \(\sim 25\%\) revenue generated from each of the smartphone, PC+ and datacenter segments, and the rest from auto (pleasant progress in 2025), wearables, robots, etc.

Reiterate OW. Huaqin has underperformed its major peer Inspr by 11ppt since fully, which we attribute to its limited revenue exposure to domestic GPU platforms and headwinds from its ESOP share disposal plan. We believe investors have been overly concerned on such impact and we expect Huaqin to ramp up its revenue on domestic GPU platform. Also, we think investors may be underestimating Huaqin's potential upside in the PC space and earnings contributions from high- margin wearables/switches. We fine tune our earnings forecasts and reiterate our OW rating with a revised Jun- 26 PT of Rmb115, based on an unchanged \(21x1\) - year forward P/E.

Huaqin Technology - A (Overweight; Price Target: Rmb115.00)

Huaqin is an original design manufacturer (ODM), with diversified exposure to smartphones, NBs, pads, wearables, AIOT and server products. We expect its core business (smartphones, notebooks and datacenters) to record solid growth and drive earnings. Meanwhile, we expect wearables, auto electronics, and robots to bring extra revenue and support long- term growth. We favor Huaqin for its sustainable growth outlook from a diversified business platform and project revenue/earnings CAGR of \(24\% /28\%\) in 2024- 27. Maintain OW.
Our Jun- 26 PT of Rmb115 is based on a 21x one- year forward P/E, on par with peers' valuation, based on JPM and Wind estimates.
